Class WithdrawalController

java.lang.Object
bto.Controllers.WithdrawalController
public class WithdrawalController extends Object
Controller class responsible for managing withdrawal requests from applicants.

This class handles the creation, approval, rejection, and management of withdrawal applications within the BTO system.

  • Method Details

    • submitWithdrawal

      public Withdrawal submitWithdrawal(Applicant applicant, ProjectApplication application)
      Submits a new withdrawal request for an applicant.

      Checks if the applicant has a valid application and if a withdrawal has not already been submitted.

      Parameters:
      applicant - The applicant requesting the withdrawal
      application - The project application to be withdrawn
      Returns:
      The created Withdrawal object, or null if the withdrawal could not be created

    • approveWithdrawal

      public boolean approveWithdrawal(Withdrawal withdrawal)
      Approves a withdrawal request.

      Updates the withdrawal status, the application status, and removes the application from the applicant's record.

      Parameters:
      withdrawal - The withdrawal to be approved
      Returns:
      true if the approval was successful, false otherwise

    • rejectWithdrawal

      public boolean rejectWithdrawal(Withdrawal withdrawal)
      Rejects a withdrawal request.

      Updates the withdrawal status and the application status.

      Parameters:
      withdrawal - The withdrawal to be rejected
      Returns:
      true if the rejection was successful, false otherwise

    • notifyApplicantStatus

      public void notifyApplicantStatus(Withdrawal withdrawal)
      Notifies an applicant about their withdrawal status.

      This is a placeholder implementation that currently outputs to the console. In a production environment, this would send notifications via email, SMS, or other means.

      Parameters:
      withdrawal - The withdrawal containing the notification information
